{
  "answer": "**Yājñavalkya Smṛti 1.4–5** (Chapter 1, translation):\n\n> Manu, Atri, Viṣṇu, Hārīta, Yājñavalkya, Uśanas, Aṅgiras,  \n> Yama, Āpastamba, Saṃvarta, Kātyāyana, and Bṛhaspati, // Yj_1.4 //  \n>   \n> Parāśara, Vyāsa, Śaṅkha, Likhita, Dakṣa, and Gautama,  \n> Śātātapa, and Vasiṣṭha are the promulgators of the Dharmaśāstras. // Yj_1.5 //[^1]\n\nThese two verses list the twenty traditional promulgators (authors) of Dharmaśāstras (legal treatises), from Manu to Vasiṣṭha.<br/>\n[^1]: *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, [paragraphs](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-0f4ad0,p-95ef53).",
